stylometry: Our group project was on chipotle mexican grill. Its problem was that their long lines and wait time was turning people away and costing them potenial revenue. The problem is that at a given time the manager can choose to have either 3-4 people on the line. We figured out that it takes 3 min a person to serve a person and we used a m/m/s queing model to show the wait time in que with 3 and 4 workers. With 4 workers the percentage of amount of people that would have to wait more than 10 min in line was drasticall smaller compared to those people who would wait inline with 3 workers working.we used m/m/s models to show both the wait time with 3 and 4 people. We then used a m/m/s optimzing model to show the costs that would incur with 4 and 3 workers working. Our findings showed that their is less cost with 3 people working compared to 4 people working(by a small margin). But in the end faster lines means more transactions and more transactions means more revenue for chipotle so we concluded that 4 people working was better than 3.
